entries.title: Russia launches a new round of attacks on the Ukrainian capital.
Benedict’s Death Leaves Catholic Conservatives Bereft
entries.description: Even after his resignation as pope, traditionalists invoked Benedict’s name and sought to draw him into internecine ideological wars. Now he is gone.

entries.title: A Balkan Leader Gets the Hollywood Treatment, Starring Kevin Spacey
entries.description: A director cast the beleaguered actor as Franjo Tudjman, the late Croatian leader, whom some call a patriot and others revile as an ethnonationalist zealot.

entries.title: Dubai Suspends Alcohol Tax as Regional Competition Heats Up
entries.description: Lower-cost liquor could help the emirate keep its edge over neighbors like Saudi Arabia and Qatar as the Middle East’s hub for leisure and business.

entries.title: U.K. Rail Strike May Scuttle Post-Holiday Plans to Return to Work
entries.description: Public sympathy for striking nurses and other health workers is particularly strong, posing a challenge for Prime Minister Rishi Sunak, who has promised to confront trade unions.

entries.title: Chance to Say Goodbye to Pope Benedict XVI Draws Thousands
entries.description: The pope emeritus is lying in state in St. Peter’s Basilica, where a long line of mourners, including Roman Catholic faithful and tourists, waited to pray and to pay last respects.

entries.title: The Question of Life Itself
entries.description: How people regard the start of life is complicated, polarizing and worthy of exploration.

entries.title: Kyiv Faces Another Night of Aerial Drone Attacks
entries.description: Explosions were heard in the capital early Monday after it once again was the target of exploding drones. In his first address of 2023, President Volodymyr Zelensky struck a defiant tone.

entries.title: 4 Dead in Helicopter Collision in Australia
entries.description: The two craft crashed in midair in a tourist area on the Gold Coast, near a theme park. An investigation is underway, with a report expected to take weeks.

entries.title: Dakar Street Style: A Photo Portfolio
entries.description: The capital of Senegal has become a fashion center. But photographing stylish people going about their day isn’t as easy as clicking a button.

entries.title: Russia’s War on Ukraine Worsens Global Starvation
entries.description: Moscow blocks most shipments from Ukraine, one of the world’s largest wheat producers, and its attacks on the country’s energy grid also disrupt the flow of food.

entries.title: ‘Biofoul’ on Hull Strands Cruise Ship at Sea for 6 Days
entries.description: An unidentified organism prompted Australia to block the vessel from docking, forcing passengers to skip a series of port stops.

entries.title: Climate Activists Find a Way to Get Germany’s Attention: Stop Traffic
entries.description: Extreme tactics have pushed the climate crisis to the top of the public discourse but also stirred debate over whether the activists are going too far.

entries.description: Lula is now the president of Brazil.
